  <div class="container">
    <h1>Peripherals</h1>
    <p>Turtles by themselves are relatively limited in how they can interact with the world. Thankfully, turtles have a way to equip <strong>tools</strong> and <strong>peripherals</strong>. Tools and peripherals can be equipped into either the turtle's left or right slot, using equipLeft and equipRight.</p> 
    <br>
    <h2>Turtle peripheral-specific functions:</h2>
    <h3>equipLeft(), equipRight()</h3>
    <p>Equip (or unequip) an item/peripheral on the left or right side of the terminal.</p>
    <p>Calling this function will attempt to equip whatever item is in the selected slot. If the slot is empty, the turtle will unequip the slot and place the equipped item into its active slot.</p>
    <br>
    <h3>Multiple other special functions can be called from the turtle via peripherals/tools, but they will be gone over in their respective chapters</h3>


